of the other, failed to sell, while its doppelg=C3=A4nger made a price 25 p=
ercent above its estimate. There are too many other factors (provenance, co=
ndition) to call this evidence of the fee structure=E2=80=99s failure, but =
it did indicate that the lower buyer=E2=80=99s premium could not overcome t=
he other factors. And even though Sotheby=E2=80=99s claimed victory in an i=
nternal email announcing the end of the lower buyer=E2=80=99s premium=E2=80=
=94which, the auction house claimed, =E2=80=9Cremoved barriers to entry for=
 new collectors and
brought greater transparency to the market, helping to drive a record numbe=
r of bidders and the strongest sell-through rates in years=E2=80=9D=E2=80=
=94I=E2=80=99ve seen data comparing the fates of 55 identical items at Soth=
eby=E2=80=99s and Christie=E2=80=99s that makes it clear the lowered buyer=
=E2=80=99s premium just wasn=E2=80=99t moving the needle.=C2=A0

