nd eventually took it public, went to federal prison for a year simply for =
<em>opening the door</em> to collusion. That said, the auction houses
have ways to signal their intentions that are legal and above board. The pr=
oblem, the auction veteran admitted, was that Sotheby=E2=80=99s came in wit=
h a =E2=80=9Chard opening bid.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Its rival seems to have felt the =
same way. I was told by someone familiar with the thinking at the top of Ch=
ristie=E2=80=99s that, in their view, Sotheby=E2=80=99s tried to do too muc=
h: re-establish the vendor=E2=80=99s commission; end enhanced hammer deals =
below $50 million; and
lower the buyer=E2=80=99s premium to 20 percent=E2=80=94too quickly. As I <=
a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktxc=
lJLZ0dUOFQ0MWNyVzJrYV9zNTRCbGJxYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvc290=
